[start section id="20112"]

Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Terry Montana' Service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Cory Zepeda, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
Preoperatively had had a discussion with Mrs. Webb that more than likely we would be recommending further chemotherapy.  I did reassure her that even though there was more than what we suspected, at this time, Dr. Montana believes that he has removed all viable disease, for sure all visible disease.  Again, I do not have pathology reports to ascertain margins and such but informed her that no matter what we would be looking at, chemotherapy following this procedure.  I stated that if there is no other evidence of any disease recurrence, in approximately one-month's time would proceed with approximately six-months worth of adjuvant therapy.  I did inform her, however, that a more definite plan will be made when she is up and allowed an appropriate recovery, typically four weeks.  I will make arrangements for her to return at that time with comprehensive lab tests and imaging studies.  They deny any further questions at this time.  They have our telephone number to contact us should they have any further questions or concerns.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

